      "paragraph_name": "COPAU0AI",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph defines the data structure COPAU0AI, which appears to be used for screen input and output. It contains various fields including TRNNAMEL, TRNNAMEF, TRNNAMEI for transaction name related data; TITLE01L, TITLE01F, TITLE01I for title information; CURDATEL, CURDATEF for current date; PAMT001L, PAMT001F, PAMT001I through PAMT005L, PAMT005F, PAMT005I for amount fields; SEL0005L, SEL0005F, SEL0005I for selection options; and ERRMSGL, ERRMSGF, ERRMSGI for error messages. The 'L' suffix likely represents the length of the field, 'F' is a flag, and 'I' is the actual data. This data structure is likely used to map data between the COBOL program and a BMS map.",
